               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="RAS_Persian_157-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied">Muhammad Mahdi al-Shirvani al-Ansari.</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Tarikh-i Mukhtasari dar Waqa'i'-i Fath-i Qistantiniyyah.</title>
                     <note>Translated from the Turkish by Muhammad Mahdi al-Shirvani al-Ansari. The date given in the colophon is stated to be that of the completion of the translation. Possibly this is the author's own copy, though it is likely that there were earlier drafts. Folio one, verso: Signature of David Price. A concise Account of the Conquest of Constantinople by Muhammad II and the early history of the City.</note>
                     <incipit>Bi-tarikh-i ghurrah- shahr-i Shawwal sanah-i 1209 Hijri</incipit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>Storey, i, p. 422. No other copy listed in Storey.</bibl>
                        <bibl>For the possible Turkish original see Franz Babinger, Die Geschichtsschreiber der Osmanen und ihre Werke, p. 30n.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian.</textLang>
                  </msItem>
